SIMPLE: off-line
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: off-line
<hw>off-line</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Computers)</fld>
<def>Not connected; -- of computers or computer peripherals normally
connected or intended to be connected to other computers by a
communications line; <as>as, we can't print the document because the
printer is <ex>off-line</ex></as>.</def> [Narrower terms:
<stype>disconnected, not ready, off</stype>; <stype>unconnected
</stype>] <ant>on-line</ant>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> offline, off line(predicate).</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <mark>(fig.)</mark> <def>Outside
of or after a meeting or formal discussion; <as>as, we can discuss the
details <ex>off-line</ex></as>; -- a term used at meetings and
conferences to suggest postponing detailed discussion of a topic so as
not to occupy the time of a large group most of whom may not be
interested.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>off-peak</ent>⟦br⟧
